reviews.text: Lovely coffee shop with great customer service and yummy food! We were a group of 10 people and everyone was very satisfied with the food and coffee. From Açai Bowl to Eggs Benedict, BLT sandwich to Blueberry or salted caramel pancakes.

Haven’t been here for a long time. This place is so popular that I don’t expect to have seats for dinner in the evening.  Food is assuringly good.

Fries as a side order is not on the menu but worth its while. The portion is good for sharing.  It is crispy and hot.
Charcoal vanilla ice cream is not too sweet!

Elephant Ground is a western style coffee shop that offers not only different types of coffees but delicious brunch varieties.  Cut animated brunch menu includes my favourite avocado toast and short rib carbatta.  I like regular cafe latte but they offer a lot of other coffee options that you cannot get in starbucks or any other coffee shop, worth a visit.
Lovely cosy place to hang out for afternoon coffee. Service was very good
Great food, wine, tea, coffee... Had one of their rice bowls in the waiters recommendation. It was fantastic. Vibe is cool.

result.name: Fashion Walk

reviews.text: This is a trendy shopping area located conveniently in Causeway Bay. There's a collection of fancy boutiques & clothing stores from various designer labels. The products are pretty high-end, meaning they could be pricier than the average store. Nonetheless, everything feels so glamorous and fashionable. This shopping area should appeal to a young demographic for sure.
Shop staff is friendly introducing the brand and they have nice product designs at KLASSE14 shop.
Small but nicely set up mall.  With Logon & Starbuck on 1st floor, I can spend a whole afternoon here. Clean washrooms on ground level. Convenient for visitors.
It has very good brands that you can't find commonly
Easy to get to & meet up with friends for a light bite & drinks. Really quaint & a nice variety to choose from. Not overly crowded too. A nice mix of eclectic groups of people and visitors.
